# Unresolved record gaps

Updated: 2026-05-18T21:34:58Z

This directory is suitable for open-record/search-enabled arbitration. It is closer to a closed-record packet than the original preliminary directory, but it remains insufficient for a clean closed-record replication.

Material gaps before a closed-record run:
- direct capture of Zelenskyy's Telegram/X confirmation of the May 9-May 11 ceasefire regime;
- direct capture of the official Ukrainian presidential decree from president.gov.ua, which returned 403 here;
- direct capture of Trump's Truth Social post or White House record, rather than media excerpts quoting it;
- direct battlefield/monitoring evidence about whether hostilities paused generally or continued materially during May 9-May 11;
- complete official Russian and Ukrainian post-period violation/implementation statements;
- if relevant, UMA proposal/dispute transaction records or Polymarket comments explaining the dispute.

Known record tension:
- The affirmative case has a wide credible-media consensus that both Russia and Ukraine confirmed a May 9-May 11 ceasefire with suspension of kinetic activity.
- The defense case has credible grounds to argue the arrangement was limited by its Victory Day, Red Square, prisoner-exchange, and alleged-violation context and therefore may not satisfy the market's "general pause" and non-humanitarian exclusions.
